modules.description: This module implements HTTP/2-based client communication for Twirp services using CoHTTP and LWT, handling request/response cycles with support for JSON or binary encoding. It works with RPC descriptors and headers as string pairs, providing functions to configure TLS, custom prefixes, and request metadata. Concrete use cases include invoking unary Twirp RPCs, inspecting errors via formatted output, and truncating debug strings for logging or diagnostics.
